{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"27":{"eng-name":"Drinks (Kitab Al-Ashribah)","ara-name":"كتاب الأشربة"}},"section_detail":{"27":{"hadithnumber_first":3669,"hadithnumber_last":3735,"arabicnumber_first":3669,"arabicnumber_last":3735}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3711,"arabicnumber":3711,"text":"A’ishah said :Dates were steeped for the Apostel of Allah (ﷺ) in skin which was tied up at the top and had a mouth. What was steeped in the morning he would drink in the evening and what was steeped in the evening he would drink in the morning","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim (2005)"}],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":43},"chapter":{"id":10,"ara-name":"باب فِي صِفَةِ النَّبِيذِ","eng-name":"Regarding the description of Nabidh","isFirstHadith":false}}]}